= Typus

Rails Plugin to create a basic and default admin interface.

Once installed and configured you can see login at http://0.0.0.0:3000/admin/

== Requirements

    script/plugin install svn://errtheblog.com/svn/plugins/will_paginate
    script/plugin install attachment_fu

NOTE: <code>attachment_fu</code> is only needed if you need uploads.

== Example Usage

To create the first user and copy the stylesheets ...

    rake typus:setup

Default user and password are +admin+ and +typus+.

== Setting your own username and password

You can set your _username_ and _password_ overwriting the following settings:

    Typus::Configuration.options[:username] = 'username'
    Typus::Configuration.options[:password] = 'password'

You can place this settings in a initializer at <code>config/initializers/typus.rb</code>.

== Configuration file options

If the configuration file is broken you'll see a +typus.yml+ text on the admin interface.

=== Typus Fields

    fields:
      list: name, created_at, category_id, status
      form: name, body, created_at, status

If you want to be able to upload data to your application add `uploaded_data` to form.

(Upload will only work with `attachment_fu`)

=== External Forms

    externals: category_id

=== Filters

    filters: status author_id created_at

=== Order

    order_by: attribute1 attribute2

=== Searches

    search: attribute1 attribute2

=== Want more actions?

    actions:
      list: notify_all
      form: notify

These actions will only be available on the context +list+ and +form+ of Typus.

=== Module

Used to group models on the main screen.

    module: Site

